# 💳 Credit Card Fraud Detection

## 📌 Project Description
This project analyzes credit card transaction data to detect **fraudulent transactions using Machine Learning**.
The goal is to identify suspicious transactions and help prevent financial loss.

Exploratory Data Analysis (**EDA**) was performed to understand the dataset.
**XGBoost model** was used to classify transactions as **fraudulent or legitimate**.

## 🔍 Analysis Performed
- Data cleaning and preprocessing
- Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
- Fraud vs normal transaction comparison
- Data visualization using **Matplotlib** and **Seaborn**

## 🤖 Model Used
**XGBoost Classifier**

The model learns patterns from transaction data and predicts whether a transaction is **fraud or normal**.

## 📊 Evaluation Metrics
- Accuracy
- Precision
- Recall
- Confusion Matrix

## 🛠 Technologies Used
- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Scikit-learn
- XGBoost
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn
- Google Colab

